The paper deals with a benchmark for commonsense reasoning about social situations, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper also discusses the crowdsourcing framework used to collect data, which could fall under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) or Computation and Society (cs.CC).
